ction.studentvote.ca/uncategorized/468',0,'revision','',0),(469,2,'2011-09-12 16:07:44','2011-09-12 16:07:44','<iframe width=\"640\" height=\"410\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/Zm4bn0BbTgs\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>','How will you increase communication with students?','','inherit','open','open','','265-revision-4','','','2011-09-12 16:07:44','2011-09-12 16:07:44','',265,'http://election.studentvote.ca/uncategorized/469',0,'revision','',0),(470,2,'2011-09-12 16:15:42','2011-09-12 16:15:42','<iframe width=\"640\" height=\"410\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/insD3PoPpiM\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>','Is the HST working?','','inherit','open','open','','268-revision-3','','','2011-09-12 16:15:42','2011-09-12 16:15:42','',268,'http://election.studentvote.ca/uncategorized/470',0,'revision','',0),(471,2,'2011-09-15 12:49:25','2011-09-15 12:49:25','<object width=\"640\" height=\"410\" id=\"s3EmbedVideo\" name=\"s3EmbedVideo\" data=\"http://releases.flowplayer.org/swf/flowplayer-3.2.7.swf\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://releases.flowplayer.org/swf/flowplayer-3.2.7.swf\" /><param name=\"allowfullscreen\" value=\"true\" /><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\" /><param name=\"flashvars\" value=\'config={\"clip\":{\"url\":\"http://video.election.studentvote.ca.s3.amazonaws.com/Leaders - Student Questions/Leaders - Question 1.mov\"},\"canvas\":{\"backgroundColor\":\"#112233\"}}}\' /></object>','What advice would you give students getting into politics?','','inherit','open','open','','270-revision-30','','','2011-09-15 12:49:25','2011-09-15 12:49:25','',270,'http://election.studentvote.ca/uncategorized/471',0,'revision','',0),(472,2,'2011-09-13 15:50:34','2011-09-13 15:50:34','<iframe width=\"640\" height=\"420\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/vKT0Ai-hEQ8\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>','Wind Turbines - Question','','inherit','open','open','','132-revision-5','','','2011-09-13 15:50:34','2011-09-13 15:50:34','',132,'http://election.studentvote.ca/uncategorized/472',0,'revision','',0),(473,2,'2011-09-14 16:01:26','2011-09-14 16:01:26','<div id=\"debate-arena-holder\">\r\n  <div class=\"position-one\">\r\n    <iframe width=\"382\" height=\"285\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/RFioA8Uf-fI\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"position-two\">\r\n   <iframe width=\"382\" height=\"285\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/wIfR78OwPy8\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"debate-arena-text\">\r\n  <div class=\"position-one\">\r\n    <div class=\"title\">Against</div>\r\nI’m John Laforet, and I’m the president of Wind Concerns Ontario.\r\n\r\nI don’t believe the province should be investing more in wind energy, and the reason for that is it’s an expensive, unreliable, and often harmful form of energy production. The Liberals are allowing turbines to be dangerously close to homes, and they generate a lot of noise because they’re about 500 feet tall, they’ve got 8,000 moving parts, and the noise they’re generating makes it very hard for people to sleep in neighbouring homes. What that’s doing is it’s resulting in a whole host of negative health effects.\r\n\r\nOn the economics, wind energy costs four times what power otherwise costs in Ontario. We’re forced to buy it even when we don’t need it, which requires us to subsidize wind developers regardless of supply and demand. What that’s doing is that’s raising everyone’s electricity bills, and we’re wasting a lot of that energy by actually paying neighbouring jurisdictions to take it from us.\r\n\r\nWind power is generated when the wind feels like generating energy, not when we need it. So what that means is we have to build natural gas plants to back up that wind. Those natural gas plants run inefficiently because they’re turned on and off very frequently, depending on what the wind is doing. It’s a very unreasonable way to structure your economy, because it results in more pollution than if you just didn’t have the wind turbines operating.\r\n\r\nWind is still unreliable and will not solve our problems, it’s not going to replace coal because it is so unreliable, so what we need to do is look at solutions to how we’re going to generate clean, affordable, and reliable power.\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"position-two\">\r\n    <div class=\"title\">For</div>\r\nMy name is Jutta Splettstoesser, I’m the president of Friends of Wind Ontario.\r\n\r\nYou can see that all around the globe, wind generation is the fastest growing energy generation. I think that speaks for itself. We have to make a plan for the future. We want to go out of coal. By 2014, we want to shut down all the coal plants. What do we use as a substitute? What are our options? One of the options is to substitute it with wind.\r\n\r\nThese are future jobs. There’s many thousands of jobs created, and will be even more created through investment in wind turbines. We need people – qualified people – engineers, builders, electricians, that will have well-paid jobs in the future. For every megawatt of wind that’s produced, it’s about 2,000 liters of water that we preserve.\r\n\r\nThere are no direct health effects proven. There could be indirect health effects, and, just recently, this summer they had the Kent research tribunal, where it was said there could be indirect health effects, but nobody died from a turbine. We will improve technology over the years as well, and you can’t do that in a vacuum. You have to try different things out.\r\n\r\n If you look at the facts, all the benefits that are out there outweigh the complaints of a minority.\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>','Wind Turbines - Debate','','inherit','open','open','','155-revision-10','','','2011-09-14 16:01:26','2011-09-14 16:01:26','',155,'http://election.studentvote.ca/uncategorized/473',0,'revision','',0),(475,2,'2011-09-14 16:40:36','2011-