ebate-arena-holder\">\r\n  <div class=\"position-one\">\r\n    <iframe width=\"382\" height=\"285\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/HptWmIu9lG4\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"position-two\">\r\n   <iframe width=\"382\" height=\"285\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/_7UvZ9x7QDk\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"debate-arena-text\">\r\n  <div class=\"position-one\">\r\n    <div class=\"title\">Against</div>\r\nI’m Deb Matthews. I’m the Minister of Health and Long-Term Care for Ontario.\r\n\r\nWe really believe in Ontario, we believe in Canada that everyone should have universal access and that means everyone should get the care they need because they need care, not because they can afford to pay for it. So for Canadians, this is kind of what makes us different than other places in the world, and I think that Canadians really value their universal health care system.\r\n\r\nIf we introduce a private component, what that means is that people with the money to pay will get care faster. It will be a shorter wait time for them, but it will be a longer wait time for everyone else. And we really do believe in equal access to care, we really do believe that we should have the best possible care for everyone, not just those who can afford to pay for it.\r\n\r\nI think we’ve come a long way in the last eight years, we’re providing much better care, more people have a family doctor now then before, our wait times are half of what they used to be. So for me, the issue is: let’s invest in our health care system so all of us get excellent care.\r\n\r\nWe only have a certain number of doctors, we only have a certain number of nurses, and if we’re pulling doctors from our publicly funded system to work in private health care, we are, by definition, reducing the resources in our public system.\r\n\r\nWhen the wait times were so long, people really were arguing for two-tier health care. We’ve come a long way in brining those wait times down. In fact, we’ve now got the shortest wait times in all of Canada, we’re meeting our targets on almost all of our surgical wait times. We now measure our wait times, we publicly report. People can go online, and see what wait times are for all the different procedures at all the different hospitals. We really track it so that we can make investments to keep those wait times down, or to get them down even lower if they’re still too high. So for me, it’s about putting the resources in the system that the system requires.\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"position-two\">\r\n    <div class=\"title\">For</div>\r\nMy name is Brian Day, I’m an orthopedic surgeon, I’m the medical director of Cambie Surgery Centre, and I’m a former President of the Canadian Medical Association. \r\n\r\nThe group in Canada that has the least access to health services and has the poorest health outcomes, are the poor. In France, in Belgium, in Switzerland, in Germany, in Austria, the rich and poor alike have rapid access to necessary health care, that the poor and underprivileged in Canada do not have. So, there are systems out there that work better than ours, that have universal health care, everyone’s covered, and they outperform us in every way.\r\n\r\nAt a big hospital in Toronto, or Vancouver, or Montreal, a patient goes to a hospital. That hospital is funded by a fixed global budget per year, say it’s a billion dollars, every patient that goes to that hospital uses up some of the money. So a patient going to a hospital is looked upon as an expense. Money should follow the patients, so a hospital that does not treat patients in an efficient and have good performance, good outcomes, is actually penalized by receiving little revenue compared to one that is efficient.\r\n\r\nMost nursing graduates in Alberta cannot get a full-time job. Many of them leave because they can’t get a full-time job. So to start saying we’ll lose manpower – we’re losing manpower now because we’re not opening our hospitals. We’re closing them at three and four o’clock in the afternoon, despite the fact that we have probably across the country over a million people waiting to get into health care. And these patients get worse while they wait.\r\n\r\nWhat we’re talking about here is a monopoly. Do you believe in a single government monopoly for any service? I don’t think monopolies serve consumers well.\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>','Wait Times - Debate','','inherit','open','open','','173-revision-8','','','2011-09-15 15:26:23','2011-09-15 15:26:23','',173,'http://election.studentvote.ca/uncategorized/529',0,'revision','',0),(530,2,'2011-09-15 16:38:32','2011-09-15 16:38:32','<div id=\"debate-arena-holder\">\r\n  <div class=\"position-one\">\r\n    <object width=\"382\" height=\"285\" id=\"s3EmbedVideo\" name=\"s3EmbedVideo\" data=\"http://releases.flowplayer.org/swf/flowplayer-3.2.7.swf\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://releases.flowplayer.org/swf/flowplayer-3.2.7.swf\" /><param name=\"allowfullscreen\" value=\"true\" /><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\" /><param name=\"flashvars\" value=\'config={\"clip\":{\"url\":\"http://video.election.studentvote.ca.s3.amazonaws.com/NEW Debates/Deb Matthews.flv\"},\"canvas\":{\"backgroundColor\":\"#112233\"}}}\' /></object>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"position-two\">\r\n   <object width=\"382\" height=\"285\" id=\"s3EmbedVideo\" name=\"s3EmbedVideo\" data=\"http://releases.flowplayer.org/swf/flowplayer-3.2.7.swf\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://releases.flowplayer.org/swf/flowplayer-3.2.7.swf\" /><param name=\"allowfullscreen\" value=\"true\" /><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\" /><param name=\"flashvars\" value=\'config={\"clip\":{\"url\":\"http://video.election.studentvote.ca.s3.amazonaws.com/NEW Debates/Brian Day.flv\"},\"canvas\":{\"backgroundColor\":\"#112233\"}}}\' /></object>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"debate-arena-text\">\r\n  <div class=\"position-one\">\r\n    <div class=\"title\">Against</div>\r\nI’m Deb Matthews. I’m the Minister of Health and Long-Term Care for Ontario.\r\n\r\nWe really believe in Ontario, we believe in Canada that everyone should have universal access and that means everyone should get the care they need because they need care, not because they can afford to pay for it. So for Canadians, this is kind of what makes us different than other places in the world, and I think that Canadians really value their universal health care system.\r\n\r\nIf we introduce a private component, what that means is that people with the money to pay will get care faster. It will be a shorter wait time for them, but it will be a longer wait time for everyone else. And we really do believe in equal access to care, we really do believe that we should have the best possible care for everyone, not just those who can afford to pay for it.\r\n\r\nI think we’ve come a long way in the last eight years, we’re providing much better care, more people have a family doctor now then before, our wait times are half of what they used to be. So for me, the issue is: let’s invest in our health care system so all of us get excellent care.\r\n\r\nWe only have a certain number of doctors, we only have a certain number of nurses, and if we’re pulling doctors from our publicly funded system to work in private health care, we are, by definition, reducing the resources in our public system.\r\n\r\nWhen the wait times were so long, people really were arguing for two-tier health care. We’ve come a long way in brining those wait times down. In fact, we’ve now got the shortest wait times in all of Canada, we’re meeting our targets on almost all of our surgical wait times. We now measure our wait times, we publicly report. People can go online, and see what wait times are for all the different procedures at all the different hospitals. We really track it so that we can make investments to keep those wait times down, or to get them down even lower if they’re still too high. So for me, it’s about putting the resources in the system that the system requires.\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"position-two\">\r\n    <div class=\"title\">For</div>\r\nMy name is Brian Day, I’m an orthopedic surgeon, I’m the medical director of Cambie Surgery Centre, and I’m a former President of the Canadian Medical Association. \r\n\r\nThe group in Canada that has the least access to health services and has the poorest health outcomes, are the poor. In France, in Belgium, in Switzerland, in Germany, in Austria, the rich and poor alike have rapid access to necessary health care, that the poor and underprivileged in Canada do not have. So, there are systems out there that work better than ours, that have universal health care, everyone’s covered, and they outperform us in every way.\r\n\r\nAt a big hospital in Toronto, or Vancouver, or Montreal, a patient goes to a hospital. That hospital is funded by a fixed global budget per year, say it’s a billion dollars, every patient that goes to that hospital uses up some of the money. So a patient going to a hospital is looked upon as an expense. Money should follow the patients, so a hospital that does not treat patients in an efficient and have good performance, good outcomes, is actually penalized by receiving little revenue compared to one that is efficient.\r\n\r\nMost nursing graduates in Alberta cannot get a full-time job. Many of them leave because they can’t get a full-time job. So to start saying we’ll lose manpower – we’re losing manpower now because we’re not opening our hospitals. We’re closing them at three and four o’clock in the afternoon, despite the fact that we have probably across the country over a million people waiting to get into health care. And these patients get worse while they wait.\r\n\r\nWhat we’re talking about here is a monopoly. Do you believe in a single government monopoly for any service? I don’t think monopolies serve consumers well.\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>','Wait Times - Debate','','inherit','open','open','','173-revision-9','','','2011-09-15 16:38:32','2011-09-15 16:38:32','',173,'http://election.studentvote.ca/uncategorized/530',0,'revision','',0),(531,2,'2011-09-15 15:24:31','2011-09-15 15:24:31','<div id=\"debate-arena-holder\">\r\n  <div class=\"position-one\">\r\n   <iframe width=\"382\" height=\"285\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/HptWmIu9lG4\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"position-two\">\r\n    <iframe width=\"382\" height=\"285\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/_7UvZ9x7QDk\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n[poll id=\"5\"]','Wait Times - Vote','','inherit','open','open','','178-revision-17','','','2011-09-15 15:24:31','2011-09-15 15:24:31','',178,'http://election.studentvote.ca/uncategorized/531',0,'revision','',0),(532,2,'2011-09-15 16:04:16','2011-09-15 16:04:16','<div class=\"leader-answer\" onclick=\"loadMovie(\'q-A0Y-_2cH4\');\">\r\n  <img src=\"http://i.imgur.com/3GgnJ.jpg\">\r\n  Green Party\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"leader-answer\" onclick=\"loadMovie(\'https://s3.amazonaws.com/video.election.studentvote.ca/Liberal+Responses/9GetIntoPolitics.mov\');\">\r\n  <img src=\"http://i.imgur.com/2jqKw.jpg\">\r\n  Liberal Party\r\n</div><div class=\"leader-answer\" onclick=\"loadMovie(\'https://s3.amazonaws.com/video.election.studentvote.ca/Special+Needs+Responses/PPSN+-+GetInvolved.mp4\');\">\r\n  <img src=\"http://i.imgur.com/t7IAN.jpg\">\r\n  Party for People with Special Needs\r\n</div><div class=\"leader-answer\" onclick=\"loadMovie(\'https://s3.amazonaws.com/video.election.studentvote.ca/Communist+Responses/Communist+-+Get+Into+PoliticsNEW.flv\');\">\r\n  <img src=\"http://i.imgur.com/k1LeM.jpg\">\r\n  Communist Party\r\n</div><div class=\"leader-answer\" onclick=\"loadMovie(\'BiBK4U8_j7c\');\">\r\n  <img src=\"h