sion','',0),(633,2,'2011-09-20 00:44:48','2011-09-20 00:44:48','<div id=\"debate-arena-holder\">\r\n  <div class=\"position-one\">\r\n    <object width=\"382\" height=\"285\" id=\"s3EmbedVideo\" name=\"s3EmbedVideo\" data=\"http://releases.flowplayer.org/swf/flowplayer-3.2.7.swf\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://releases.flowplayer.org/swf/flowplayer-3.2.7.swf\" /><param name=\"allowfullscreen\" value=\"true\" /><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\" /><param name=\"flashvars\" value=\'config={\"clip\":{\"url\":\"http://video.election.studentvote.ca.s3.amazonaws.com/Hate Crimes : HST/Chris Delaney.mov.flv\", \"autoPlay\":false},\"canvas\":{\"backgroundColor\":\"#112233\"}}}\' /></object>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"position-two\">\r\n   <object width=\"382\" height=\"285\" id=\"s3EmbedVideo\" name=\"s3EmbedVideo\" data=\"http://releases.flowplayer.org/swf/flowplayer-3.2.7.swf\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://releases.flowplayer.org/swf/flowplayer-3.2.7.swf\" /><param name=\"allowfullscreen\" value=\"true\" /><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\" /><param name=\"flashvars\" value=\'config={\"clip\":{\"url\":\"http://video.election.studentvote.ca.s3.amazonaws.com/Hate Crimes : HST/Dwight Duncan.flv\", \"autoPlay\":false},\"canvas\":{\"backgroundColor\":\"#112233\"}}}\' /></object>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"debate-arena-text\">\r\n  <div class=\"position-one\">\r\n    <div class=\"title\">Against</div>\r\nChris Delaney, lead organizer of Fight HST.\r\n\r\nThe HST actually has a very significant impact on people. Particularly low-income people like high school students, like seniors, like the unemployed, middle-income families- they pay the bigger portion of their share of income in taxes through an HST. That applies to everyone, no matter who you are. So if you\'re making $100,000 or $200,000 dollars a year, you pay seven per cent on a cup of coffee at Tim Hortons, and if you\'re making $10,000 a year, you pay seven per cent on a cup of coffee at Tim Hortons. So the guy that\'s not making as much money, it takes a greater portion of his income to support that tax.\r\n\r\nGiven that Canada today is a service-based economy, putting a tax on services actually reduces consumption of those services, so it harms the economy.\r\n\r\nWell, they say it will create more jobs, it will stimulate the economy. So you might go, \"Okay, well, if that\'s the case I don\'t mind paying a little bit of tax because then I\'ll get a job.\" But everywhere the HST comes in, and everywhere the value added tax comes in, unemployment goes up. It actually is a job killer. Why? Because it reduces consumption.\r\n\r\nIf you want to look at economies that are stimulated in Canada right now. The three strongest economies are: Alberta, Saskatchewan, and Manitoba. They have unemployment in the five per cent range, they have new economic development going on there, they have one of the lowest per capita debt situations, and lowest cost of living, and there\'s no HST in any one of those three provinces.\r\n\r\nThe polls there show 75% of the people there don\'t like it. And yet, here have a political party that, you\'d think it would be a no-brainer to say, \"Get rid of it!\" And they\'ll be elected. But none of them have the guts. And they didn\'t have the guts here either by the way, so the citizens rose up and we revolted. \r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"position-two\">\r\n    <div class=\"title\">For</div>\r\nDwight Duncan, member of Provincial Parliament for Windsor-Tecumseh.\r\n\r\nWe created something called a tax plan for jobs and growth where we\'ve actually lowered taxes for 93% of Ontarians, because we cut personal taxes when we did this, we cut the tax rate on the first $37,000 dollars of income when we brought in the HST.\r\n\r\nIn the old PST, you couldn\'t see it but there was tax on tax on tax. And so what this does is it unlocks that. So let me give you an example, I often use my watch as an example. On your watch you\'ve got the band, you\'ve got the glass casing, you\'ve got the inner-workings. And each one of those is made separately. If you were a watchmaker, you would pay a provincial sales tax on all of it. What this does, what the HST does, it takes all that tax off and gives it to the business. So the only time you pay the tax is at the end, the consumer.\r\n\r\nSince we\'ve implemented the HST, it\'s been a little over a year now, we\'ve seen about 114,000 new jobs. It\'s all part of a tax package, so we cut other taxes, we created a very generous sales tax credit. In fact, students and young people would probably be among the biggest beneficiaries because we cut the tax rate on the first $37,000 dollars of income.\r\n\r\nWherever they\'ve implemented a value added tax, which is what the HST is, businesses lower their prices eventually to reflect the fact that they\'re paying less in hidden tax. And so there\'s no debate about that, it happens. \r\n  </div>\r\n</div>','HST - Debate','','publish','open','open','','hst-debate','','','2011-09-20 02:07:14','2011-09-20 02:07:14','',0,'http://election.studentvote.ca/?p=633',0,'post','',0),(634,2,'2011-09-19 21:44:14','2011-09-19 21:44:14','','HST - Debate','','inherit','open','open','','633-revision','','','2011-09-19 21:44:14','2011-09-19 21:44:14','',633,'http://election.studentvote.ca/uncategorized/634',0,'revision','',0),(635,2,'2011-09-19 21:47:53','2011-09-19 21:47:53','<div id=\"debate-arena-holder\">\n  <div class=\"position-one\">\n    <object width=\"382\" height=\"285\" id=\"s3EmbedVideo\" name=\"s3EmbedVideo\" data=\"http://releases.flowplayer.org/swf/flowplayer-3.2.7.swf\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://releases.flowplayer.org/swf/flowplayer-3.2.7.swf\" /><param name=\"allowfullscreen\" value=\"true\" /><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\" /><param name=\"flas