se of his or her race, faith, sexual orientation, gender, or other characteristics – are on the rise. Many cities in Ontario (from major urban centres like Toronto, Ottawa, and London, to smaller communities such as Peterborough and Guelph) reported more hate crimes in 2010 than in the years before. Part of this increase is due to the fact that more people are reporting hate crimes to police than they used to (especially now that more people are aware of what hate crimes are, and how serious they are), but crimes against specific minorities also tend to increase when the economy dips.\r\n\r\nOntario is one of the most diverse regions in the world, with people from just about every country and religion settling here. This makes the need to confront hate crimes in this province all the more pressing. And while hate crimes are still relatively few and far between, their impact on communities – whether it\'s swastikas painted on a synagogue, or a man getting beaten up just because he\'s gay – is often far greater than the impact of typical offences. When hate crimes are committed, the victims (and the religious, gender, ethnic, or other groups that they represent) are made to feel unwelcome, and often live in fear of being targeted for future crimes.\r\n\r\nDespite the rising number of hate crimes in Ontario, none of the three major political parties have any specific plans for tackling the problem. Regardless, some authorities on the subject say the key to getting rid of hate crimes is to educate the population about the differences among Ontario\'s many minority groups, so that those differences are no longer seen as “other.” On the other hand, some people suggest there should be harsher punishments for those convicted of hate crimes, since this could discourage others from committing similar crimes. There is much debate over the best way to address this serious issue, but the evidence is clear: Something must be done. Given what you’ve learned, what do you think is the best way to combat hate crimes in Ontario?','Hate Crimes / Cyber Bullying','','inherit','open','open','','248-revision-6','','','2011-09-19 15:55:12','2011-09-19 15:55:12','',248,'http://election.studentvote.ca/uncategorized/653',0,'revision','',0),(654,2,'2011-09-20 00:29:26','2011-09-20 00:29:26','<div id=\"debate-arena-holder\">\r\n  <div class=\"position-one\">\r\n    <object width=\"382\" height=\"285\" id=\"s3EmbedVideo\" name=\"s3EmbedVideo\" data=\"http://releases.flowplayer.org/swf/flowplayer-3.2.7.swf\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://releases.flowplayer.org/swf/flowplayer-3.2.7.swf\" /><param name=\"allowfullscreen\" value=\"true\" /><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\" /><param name=\"flashvars\" value=\'config={\"clip\":{\"url\":\"http://video.election.studentvote.ca.s3.amazonaws.com/Hate Crimes : HST/Karen Mock.flv\", \"autoPlay\":false},\"canvas\":{\"backgroundColor\":\"#112233\"}}}\' /></object>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"position-two\">\r\n   <object width=\"382\" height=\"285\" id=\"s3EmbedVideo\" name=\"s3EmbedVideo\" data=\"http://releases.flowplayer.org/swf/flowplayer-3.2.7.swf\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://releases.flowplayer.org/swf/flowplayer-3.2.7.swf\" /><param name=\"allowfullscreen\" value=\"true\" /><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\" /><param name=\"flashvars\" value=\'config={\"clip\":{\"url\":\"http://video.election.studentvote.ca.s3.amazonaws.com/Hate Crimes : HST/Craig Jones.flv\", \"autoPlay\":false},\"canvas\":{\"backgroundColor\":\"#112233\"}}}\' /></object>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"debate-arena-text\">\r\n  <div class=\"position-one\">\r\n    <div class=\"title\">Against</div>\r\nVideo transcript 1. Karen Mock.\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"position-two\">\r\n    <div class=\"title\">For</div>\r\nVideo transcript 2. Craig Jones.\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>','Hate Crimes - Debate','','inherit','op