 Until then, you can check out a demo of what the live discussion will look like:\r\n</div>\r\n<iframe src=\"http://www.coveritlive.com/index2.php/option=com_altcaster/task=viewaltcast/altcast_code=d01cd14c81/height=900/width=550\" scrolling=\"no\" height=\"900px\" width=\"550px\" frameborder=\"0\" allowtransparency=\"true\">&lt;a href=\"http://www.coveritlive.com/mobile.php/option=com_mobile/task=viewaltcast/altcast_code=d01cd14c81\" &gt;CoveritLive Demo&lt;/a&gt;</iframe>\r\n</div>\r\n','Events','','inherit','open','open','','80-revision-16','','','2011-09-23 15:53:47','2011-09-23 15:53:47','',80,'http://election.studentvote.ca/uncategorized/775',0,'revision','',0),(776,2,'2011-09-23 19:13:21','2011-09-23 19:13:21','<object width=\"640\" height=\"420\" id=\"s3EmbedVideo\" name=\"s3EmbedVideo\" data=\"http://releases.flowplayer.org/swf/flowplayer-3.2.7.swf\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://releases.flowplayer.org/swf/flowplayer-3.2.7.swf\" /><param name=\"allowfullscreen\" value=\"true\" /><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\" /><param name=\"flashvars\" value=\'config={\"clip\":{\"url\":\"http://video.election.studentvote.ca.s3.amazonaws.com/Obesity Health/3_Gym.mov.flv\"},\"canvas\":{\"backgroundColor\":\"#112233\"}}}\' /></object>','Obesity / Health - Question','','publish','open','open','','obesity-health-question','','','2011-09-23 19:38:08','2011-09-23 19:38:08','',0,'http://election.studentvote.ca/?p=776',0,'post','',0),(777,2,'2011-09-23 19:13:14','2011-09-23 19:13:14','','Obesity / Health - Question','','inherit','open','open','','776-revision','','','2011-09-23 19:13:14','2011-09-23 19:13:14','',776,'http://election.studentvote.ca/uncategorized/777',0,'revision','',0),(778,2,'2011-09-23 19:14:09','2011-09-23 19:14:09','<div id=\"debate-arena-holder\">\r\n  <div class=\"position-one\">\r\n    <object width=\"382\" height=\"285\" id=\"s3EmbedVideo\" name=\"s3EmbedVideo\" data=\"http://releases.flowplayer.org/swf/flowplayer-3.2.7.swf\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://releases.flowplayer.org/swf/flowplayer-3.2.7.swf\" /><param name=\"allowfullscreen\" value=\"true\" /><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\" /><param name=\"flashvars\" value=\'config={\"clip\":{\"url\":\"http://video.election.studentvote.ca.s3.amazonaws.com/Obesity Health/Kevin Wamsley.flv\", \"autoPlay\":false},\"canvas\":{\"backgroundColor\":\"#112233\"}}}\' /></object>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"position-two\">\r\n   <object width=\"382\" height=\"285\" id=\"s3EmbedVideo\" name=\"s3EmbedVideo\" data=\"http://releases.flowplayer.org/swf/flowplayer-3.2.7.swf\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://releases.flowplayer.org/swf/flowplayer-3.2.7.swf\" /><param name=\"allowfullscreen\" value=\"true\" /><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\" /><param name=\"flashvars\" value=\'config={\"clip\":{\"url\":\"http://video.election.studentvote.ca.s3.amazonaws.com/Obesity Health/Melanie Slade.flv\", \"autoPlay\":false},\"canvas\":{\"backgroundColor\":\"#112233\"}}}\' /></object>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"debate-arena-text\">\r\n  <div class=\"position-one\">\r\n    <div class=\"title\">Against</div>\r\nKevin Wamsley, Associate Dean, Health Sciences, University of Western Ontario.\r\n\r\nPeople get together and when they go to high school for the first time, all the sudden they have to put shorts and t-shirt on for the first time, they have to change in front of other people. If their body doesn\'t fit the ideal image of what we\'re led to believe is the perfect body, then they\'re generally open to harassment.\r\n\r\nGenerally, what our research shows is that they are not enjoying the environment in the class. So they don\'t think they fit in, they see hierarchies in the classroom, people make fun of them, there\'s a little bit of harassment, bullying.  But for those who aren\'t bullied or harassed, they just feel like they are unable to succeed in the classroom based on the environment that\'s there. So for grade nine boys, this is a real tough environment. So the locker room is a problem.\r\n\r\nThe class becomes a problem in a traditional sports environment. For the last 40 years, we\'ve been teaching kids how to play traditional sports, and in that model, the best always rise to the top. and the others are left behind. We have to have an environment where everyone can succeed and enjoy themselves, that\'s first. So we\'d have to teach kids that physical activity is fun, and everyone can participate in physical activity of some sort. We need to have choices, so there\'s not just traditional sports like football, volleyball, rugby, and basketball.\r\n\r\nPeople have had negative issues in grade nine and grade 10 gym classes, and that\'s why they\'ve left them. So if we force them to go through grade 12 without making curriculum changes, we run the risk of alienating a large percentage of our population. They\'re giving up exercise, they\'re giving up fitness, they\'re giving up healthy lifestyle, and they\'re turning to other things that interest them.\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"position-two\">\r\n    <div class=\"title\">For</div>\r\nMelanie Slade, Communications Leader, Ontario Physical and Health Education Association.\r\n\r\nPhys-ed, gym, or health and phys-ed as we like to call it here, is important and should be mandatory because it helps students develop the skills that they need for the rest of their lives. It\'s not about sports, and it\'s not about learning to play basketball, or learning to play volleyball, it\'s about learning to be healthy active individuals throughout the lifespan.\r\n\r\nThere\'s a lot of research out there that indicates children and youth in Canada and Ontario are not getting enough physical activity. One report, it\'s called the Active Healthy Kids Canada Report Card on Physical Activity for Children and Youth, and it has shown year after year that kids are not getting enough. This past year it showed that only nine per cent of boys and only four per cent of girls get enough physical activity, as recommended by the Canadian physical activity guidelines.\r\n\r\nHaving mandatory phys-ed class every day would help to address that for sure. But it would also teach kids the things they need to do outside of school and outside of that class in order to make sure that they are making the right choices and healthy choices. \r\n\r\nHealthy students and active students are better learners. They\'re more productive, there\'s less absenteeism from other classes, there\'s less stress, they know how to cope with stress better. A lot of different things like that, that can actually help in the other areas of school.\r\n\r\nThe skills that you learn in health and phys-ed, whether its nutrition, whether its how to be physically active in a healthy way, whether it is positive body image and mental health, those are things that you take with you throughout your life. That\'s where it could really benefit students.\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>','Obesity / Health - Debate','','publish','open','open','','obesity-health-debate','','','2011-09-23 20:08:27','2011-09-23 20:08:27','',0,'http://election.studentvote.ca/?p=778',0,'post','',0),(779,2,'2011-09-23 19:14:07','2011-09-23 19:14:07','','Obesity / Health - Debate','','inherit','open','open','','778-revision','','','2011-09-23 19:14:07','2011-09-23 19:14:07','',778,'http://election.studentvote.ca/uncategorized/779',0,'revision','',0),(780,2,'2011-09-23 19:14:20','2011-09-23 19:14:20','<script>\r\nvar idcomments_acct = \'066bba3582108cb66ff7a183c5e6a3b0\';\r\nvar idcomments_post_id;\r\nvar idcomments_post_url;\r\n</script>\r\n<span id=\"IDCommentsPostTitle\" style=\"display:none\"></span>\r\n<script type=\'text/javascript\' src=\'http://www.intensedebate.com/js/genericCommentWrapperV2.js\'></script>','Obesity / Health - Comment','','publish','open','ope