23 19:27:18','2011-09-23 19:27:18','',782,'http://election.studentvote.ca/uncategorized/795',0,'revision','',0),(796,2,'2011-09-23 19:48:44','2011-09-23 19:48:44','One in four students in Canada is considered overweight, and that number is expected to rise in the coming years. Unbalanced diets and inactive lifestyles are a big part of the reason Canada\'s getting fat, and they pose long-term threats to Ontario\'s health-care system. Overweight and obese people are more likely to develop heart disease, diabetes, depression, and a raft of other issues than those with healthier body weights. As if a rapidly aging population wasn\'t straining the health-care system enough, the looming obesity crisis only stands to complicate matters.\r\n\r\nFinding a way to curb the growth of Ontarians\' waistlines is a tricky proposition. The government can\'t simply tell people what they should and shouldn\'t eat. However, there are ways to encourage citizens to lead healthier lifestyles. One proposal is that all students should be required to take gym classes throughout their entire school career, as getting young people to develop healthy habits such as exercising is seen as one of the best ways to help them ward off obesity for the rest of their lives. Other suggestions include posting the calorie counts of meals on restaurant menus, banning junk food in schools, and making healthier foods – especially fruits and vegetables – more affordable for more people.\r\n\r\nSo far in this election, the New Democratic Party has proposed introducing mandatory gym class, forcing chain restaurants to display their food’s nutritional information, and banning junk-food advertisements aimed at kids. The Liberals want to launch a “Council on Childhood Obesity” that would aim to bring obesity levels in children down by 20 per cent, while the Progressive Conservatives haven\'t touched the issue yet. What do you think: Would measures like mandatory gym class help the province get in shape?','Obesity / Health','','inherit','open','open','','235-autosave','','','2011-09-23 19:48:44','2011-09-23 19:48:44','',235,'http://election.studentvote.ca/uncategorized/796',0,'revision','',0),(797,2,'2011-09-23 19:39:06','2011-09-23 19:39:06','<div id=\"debate-arena-holder\">\r\n  <div class=\"position-one\">\r\n    <object width=\"382\" height=\"285\" id=\"s3EmbedVideo\" name=\"s3EmbedVideo\" data=\"http://releases.flowplayer.org/swf/flowplayer-3.2.7.swf\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://releases.flowplayer.org/swf/flowplayer-3.2.7.swf\" /><param name=\"allowfullscreen\" value=\"true\" /><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\" /><param name=\"flashvars\" value=\'config={\"clip\":{\"url\":\"http://video.election.studentvote.ca.s3.amazonaws.com/Obesity Health/Kevin Wamsley.flv\", \"autoPlay\":false},\"canvas\":{\"backgroundColor\":\"#112233\"}}}\' /></object>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"position-two\">\r\n   <object width=\"382\" height=\"285\" id=\"s3EmbedVideo\" name=\"s3EmbedVideo\" data=\"http://releases.flowplayer.org/swf/flowplayer-3.2.7.swf\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://releases.flowplayer.org/swf/flowplayer-3.2.7.swf\" /><param name=\"allowfullscreen\" value=\"true\" /><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\" /><param name=\"flashvars\" value=\'config={\"clip\":{\"url\":\"http://video.election.studentvote.ca.s3.amazonaws.com/Obesity Health/Melanie Slade.flv\", \"autoPlay\":false},\"canvas\":{\"backgroundColor\":\"#112233\"}}}\' /></object>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"debate-arena-text\">\r\n  <div class=\"position-one\">\r\n    <div class=\"title\">Against</div>\r\nKevin Wamsley transcript.\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class=\"position-two\">\r\n    <div class=\"title\">For</div>\r\nMelanie Slade transcript.\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>','Obesity / Health - Debate','','inherit','open','open','','778-revision-4','','','2011-09-23 19:39:06','2011-09-23 19:39:06'